content: Great visual entertainment for your cat(s) that delights their inner need to wack things. It's fun watching them have fun. Be a good cat mommy or daddy and give your kitty the environmental stimulation it needs.ðŸ˜‰
Cats love it!

Good but needs more customization. Would like an x on the menu screen to close. The button to go to menu needs to be more than 1/2 the size. You should be able to tell it only one wack a mole at a time and more than one shark. Speed settings for all of them. Make it over ride tablet time out. I have one cat that just likes to watch it like a tv.
My cats LOVE this. They request it, meowing and pawing the tablet every night. They beat each others high scores. They play it together. Got a lot of hours out of this so far

My cat loves this game. I find it annoying since she keeps ending up back at the main screen. You should make it more difficult for someone to return to the main menu than a rapid double tap. To catch those mice my cat taps the glass.
Its a good game!! My cats havent tryed it yet hopefully they like it!
Why is the back button so big on the games?

Amazing app. It works exactly as advertised. My adult cats go crazy for these games. I have spent so much more on stuff they have never played with. Also, the bigger your screen the better, and use a screen protector. Cats have claws.
My cat loves this game, specifically she greatly enjoys the catch the mouse on cheese version of this game. She plays it for long stretches of time and seems to find it very satisfying.
My cats have loved this game for YEARS!!! they can not get enough of the fish!! Lol

Two Paws Up! I wouldn't let Mommy play with her nice Nexus tablet. I clawed and ate at the case, too. And I erased apps off the home screen, and caused other mischief in my excitement, too. So Mom bought me a cheap tablet of my own and got me my own Google account, so I couldn't mess with her Play Store apps anymore. I knocked that tablet off the bed so many times it broke. So Mom just bought me a new $39 RCA from Wally World! And Cat Playground is still around! Am I a lucky kitty or what? MEOW! Now if the lovely developers would make it so I can't hit the back, home, and recent icons......
My cats and my friend's cats of varying ages all love this
My cat is just playing and the screen leaves her.
I'd keep the sound off but my cat loves this, especially the mouse.
When my cats are in a playful mood they love it. I found kittens enjoy the games even more. The home screen graphics could be updated but otherwise the simple graphics work well with cats.
All my cats like it and some people... Lol
I can see certain cats interacting with this game, but too bad my cat just watched it the whole time and didn't even try to interact with it :(
Our kitty loves this app!  The mouse chase is his favorite.
Please remove the vibration when she taps the laser pointer :D. It scares her a bit hehe
My cat loves this game so much and she swats it until she can play it :D

I originally purchased on my phone and the cats didn't really care but they are obsessed with the game on the tablet! They hear the music and come running! Both cats play with toys not hands. My Ralphy recently pawed at my phone and tablet hoping to turn them on so he could play! Fragile Ralphy! Fragile! He thinks they're his!

My cats are both now 7 months old. The female has no interest, but the male cat ears pick up as soon as he hears the music. He loved it, especially the fish in a tank game, I also like that one best as the running water sound effect is actually very relaxing when on in the background.

Note 4: The other games were ok for my cats, the laser game also did better than the others.  I'm sure other cats might enjoy the other games, not all cats are the same. No adds, worth the money. Exited once in about 10-15 mins of play, was the multiple apps/menu button on NOTE 4. No permissions needed is a plus too.

Kitten loves it, really loved the mouse. So much so that every time she sees my phone she states at it and sniffs, and bats at it, probably hoping the mouse will show up. UPDATE Screen mirroring to my Sony Bravia TV, my cat went bezerk! hilarious!

I bought this for Kari, our 15 year old Burmese. She's not into playing much these days, and she's very deaf but the Mouse game really got her attention and she was looking under the tablet to try to get to it.
I had my doubts, but the reviews were good so I gave it a go....and we were not disappointed. The kittens LOVE it! Amazing
They love it!
I bought this for my cats, but ended up being more amused by watching them play with it than they are playing!
My cat is mesmerized by the sharks.  This app is his favorite. The vibration and sounds are great.  This apps a keeper.
He plays with it all the time.

Thank you. My 10 month old kitten Sparta loves this game. All I have to do is turn it on and the second she hears the music she comes running.  Watching her reach behind the tablet to try to cheat and get the mouse is too funny.  My 2 year old  cat Tinkerbell isn't fooled and loses interest in the games quickly.
He loves it....
I got bored and downloaded this for my cat. She enjoys playing it so much she pounces on my phone any time something moves on it (like my finger)

Arthur absolutely adores our pad now. He can play for hours, and this is perfect for when he is being annoying and needs to use up some energy. However, he keeps pressing the home and back-buttons, and still looking for the mouse, he starts pressing all sorts of stuff. Add a screen lock of some sort, and the game is perfect!

I think I've installed every cat game possible and this one is by far my cat's absolute favorite.  He will play with the mouse one for hours and hours.  I did have to install a program called full!screen so he can't even access the soft menus (works amazingly well) and yet he still manages to sometimes his the side power button or the one physical home button on my Nook HD+.
Keeps wee Hamlet occupied for hours.  If there was a means of locking out the home, back and recent apps buttons this would be perfect
Jack black is getting the hang of this touch screen game! So fun to watch how focused he gets. The mouse is his favorite! Thanks!
This really works on one of my cats - she absolutely loves the dot and the mouse.  I need another phone for the cat now!
No refund!!!!!
I bought this today, after 10 minutes of watching my cat started killing the red dot. He loves it!
My cat loves to chase the mouse!
My cat loves it :-)
Even the old ones!
She never gets bored with it. I have as much fun watching her as she does playing the game.
My cat loves this!! Hilarious watching him play! Love that it keeps his scores as well.
She made me come give it a 4 star rating. I had no choice she's the boss.
My cats are curious about it but don't really play with it.

My cat loves this app. He gets so jealous when I'm on my phone or my tablet. Buying this app was so worth it. When my cat has extra energy before I go to bed I turn on the app and his gets a kick out of it. Make sure to buy a screen protector before using.
Leaving game by pressing two cats on screen rarely works. No options anymore to turn sound off... what were they thinking?
Muy bueno
Back button doesn't work and target doesn't vibrate when hit.

Suggestion: make the mouse or fish stay under the border longer. My cat's much more intrigued when I cover half the tablet with a newspaper, hiding the mouse for several seconds until it reappears again.
Now you have to hit the two cats to go back and that doesn't work! I want to be able to go back to the menu!
She tries to bite my phone loves the laser wonders why it's not on the other side of the phone :-)
My cats love this!  Makes me smile watching them play.
My cats really seem to enjoy this game. However, even though you have to hit the back button twice to get out, the menu button works normally. My kitten has mastered closing this game.
My cats love this app!  One of them loves watching the fish while the other has become an expert as the treat game.  Highly recommend for all spoiled cats.

A few tips: Do not let the cat attempt to eat or scratch your device without the device having a glass protector and case to protect it...   Having a couple of elderly cats that love sitting on my keyboard, this was a great test to give them something to do while I work from home.   My attack cat loved the mouse game, tried to get under the tablet and eat the mouse several times. However he can close the app easily or change screens then send blank emails or reply to emails and txts...  He liked the whack a mouse game too but the contrast on the screen seemed off to me the killer cat did try to dig under the tablet screen and case to get to the mice.   My laser pointer cat didn't catch onto the laser game but the non laser pointer cat did watch for a bit.   The fish level got a couple of swipes and bites on the screen (he's caught actual fish in a tank that way) but then a shrug and no more action.  The toy game also got a few whacks but then not much interest after a full pounce and bite on the screen.  The Nexus 7 tablet on the floor now but neither cat is bored enough to watch it yet. Does need a trial version though or make it 99 cents.

My cat loves the fish and the creepy wack-a-moles. She tries to dig the moles out of the holes, and reaches underneath the Xoom trying to get them. I may need to replace my screen protector eventually, but its so cute when she plays.
Cute to watch, cell phone is not recommended, use with tablet
I was really excited about this app but my cats were not interested at all.
Especially mouse..
...the software buttons on my Nexus 7 needs to inactivated. When the cat hits the home button the fun ends. I've tried to tell her to stop hitting it, but in vain.
Our cats love it!!!

my kittens sort of got it although the more complicated the screen(whack) the less they got it. apparently cats cant see too much detail, more movement.  so the laser, fish, treats and mouse are better because of the simplicity.....more screens like that would be much better and made it a five
I tried this and my kitten was interested, but his presses didn't register. Tried myself, mine didn't register either most of the time! Needs a trial version, e.g. limited to 2 minutes a game.
I was slightly sceptical but actually found that even my laziest cat enjoyed watching the mouse, he didn't move much apart from his eyes but even that is good for him :D
I think my cat spends more time with my tablet than I do. He's not complaining so why should I?
Since update won't run fix soon bad rsteing until fixed.   Update reinstall by uninstalling the a full reinstall fixed the problem
Latest update makes app instant force close on Nexus 7.
My kittens love this app.
All 7 of my cats are totally brainless and don't react.  Hehe.
My cat loved them all, especially the whale type fish thing, the one that splits off into other things and the mouse lol

She was immediatey interested and she really got into the cheese/mouse game. I think the sound was exciting for her. It was funny watching her play too. Great app, although it could use sounds on more of the games.

My cat minky wasn't interested prob cause my phone is got a small screen  she's olny a year old and she didn't seem to understand I tryed but she climbed the wardrobe instead silly kitty but I loved it
Worst toy ever. I wasted money on this application. My cat chewed my phone and then bit me. Now im bleeding and i am short two dollars. Would not recommend.

I just downloaded the "Cat Playground" app for my Android tablet.  None of the younger cats were interested, but Sprinkles, their mother, loved it.  She and I took turns catching the 'fish'.  I didn't know if she was going to let me have it back. :-)  She liked the fish best, although the mouse on the cheese was a close second.  I think it needs more sound, though.  As far as I could tell, only the cheese game had sound.  In the absence of physical feedback, that seems important.  Nook Color running Cyanogenmod.  (There's no vibrate on this device, so maybe that's why some of the games are silent.  If so, it might be nice to be able to select speaker sound instead.)
Kinda works, my cats interested, they attacked it once, so it not a fail, my cats just lazy
For real
My nuggets love this! But my one tardo one tries to catch the fish from behind the phone.
Cat loves this as much as the ipad cat paint app. I only wish that the cat could paint with this one too.
It is sprung to watch my Kitty! I reccomend this for cats who like to scratch and play. My cat seems to only like the fish one. She's gotten 600 points!
Not only is it on my tablet for my cat who loves it but it is also on my phone and my two month old daughter loves the fish and mouse thanks

My cat loves playing it, but selecting items in the menu is near impossible. I have to tap multiple times to get it to respond. Often I have to give up and force the application to close. Galaxy tab 10.1.
My cat ignored it. When I tried to get her interested, she chewed on my phone case instead.

My cat loves this app.  If only he could play it for more than 30 seconds before exiting the app.  if i'm going to have to fix my tab for him every other minute, I might as well be playing with him myself
Won't open, please give me my $$ back!! DroidX
Okay, well actually I love watching my cat play with this on my tablet. Mouse and fish seem to work best.
My two cats loved it, mouse chase was the favorite with laser pointer a close second. Now theylook excited whenever I pick up my tablet.

It took 5 minutes to down load, and 5 minutes to see that my cart didn't want a thing to do with it. When I went to get my refund it said I was too late. That was NO 15!  Congratulations you got me.  Do not download this trap.
My 12 year old cat loves this app thanks guys, Great idea :)

This is a great idea, and my cats got the hang of it right away.  I do wish the touchscreen was more responsive, because sometimes the hit the mouse but the mouse is still there, which frustrates them.  Moto Xoom wifi on ICS.
One of my cats loves it, the other one doesn't care.  It's really cute either way :-)
My cat sits ans plays this for hours, she begs for this game when we get home. Its so funny to watch her play.
and buy it already. Meow.
I got good laughs out of this app, cats reaction is hilarious. Worth every penny
Works, but could use more games

The apps is good and do very well wat it is designed for, entertain the cat ( and sometimes the owners ). Work great on TF201 on ICS there's something weird when the apps start the screen flash with some weird color, but once it's loaded everything is ok... I got two sugestions: 1- Would be great to keep at least the top score ;) The cat don't care about it but it could be fun to see if he improve his score with time and practice!. 2- Ok this one is probably hard, I was wondering if it could be possible to use the front camera on the tablet to "detect" the cat movement or at least proximity and alter the way the fish,laser,mouse is moving ? I think this could make them crazy!
I have this on my phone till I get my tablet, kitty loves it regardless. The laser one is his favorite!
Me gusta, Sinforoso, el gato (I like it, Sinforoso the cat)
Please make the buttons on the title screen larger. They are far too small. Also, add an option to disable vibration. It scares my cat.
Turns out I just don't know how to use the market properly, app works great. Our cat loves the games, especially the mouse one! Great email support offered by the developer too, very friendly.
